nars.util.event

Class ArraySharingList<C>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nars.util.event.ArraySharingList<C>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<C>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DefaultTopic

    public class ArraySharingList<C>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable<C>
    Thread safe list which produces arrays for fast iteration these arrays are like copy-on-write-array-list except are reusable and null-terminated (and padded). so if the size shrinks, it does not need to reallocate. null padding is applied to assist garbage collection fully unless the synchronized methods are used, udpates may contain inconsistent data. use C[] nullTerminatedArray() to access this array, don't change it without a good reason (it will be shared), and iterate it in sequence and stop at the first null (this is the end).
